48
00:02:01,680 --> 00:02:04,840
The first is recombination.

49
00:02:04,840 --> 00:02:08,620
Recombination is the mixing of
your DNA, if you're one of the

50
00:02:08,620 --> 00:02:11,689
parents, with the DNA
of the other parent.

51
00:02:11,689 --> 00:02:14,259
From an evolutionary
perspective, recombination

52
00:02:14,259 --> 00:02:17,599
means you pass on less of your
own DNA, but you may be

53
00:02:17,599 --> 00:02:20,590
passing it on into more
viable offspring.

54
00:02:20,590 --> 00:02:22,550
First and probably foremost,

55
00:02:22,550 --> 00:02:24,960
recombination produces variation.

56
00:02:24,960 --> 00:02:27,640
Because of recombination,
offspring are not identical

57
00:02:27,639 --> 00:02:29,409
clones of either of
their parents.

58
00:02:29,409 --> 00:02:31,409
They're a new mixture
of the DNA.

59
00:02:31,409 --> 00:02:34,049
And even in the case of
identical twins, there are

60
00:02:34,050 --> 00:02:37,280
slight genetic differences
between all the offspring.

61
00:02:37,280 --> 00:02:41,930
Recombination also allows new
genetic variation, new traits

62
00:02:41,930 --> 00:02:45,560
