from one to another

68
00:03:02,409 --> 00:03:04,539
to try to get the
same advantage.

69
00:03:04,539 --> 00:03:06,699
Recombination can also
act as a kind of

70
00:03:06,699 --> 00:03:08,549
genetic repair mechanism.

71
00:03:08,550 --> 00:03:10,830
Because you can get copies of
a gene from both of your

72
00:03:10,830 --> 00:03:13,469
parents, if one of them is
defective, there's a

73
00:03:13,469 --> 00:03:16,020
possibility that it won't
be a fatal flaw.

74
00:03:16,020 --> 00:03:19,719
This allows us to kind of
clean up certain genetic

75
00:03:19,719 --> 00:03:22,270
defects over time through
recombination.

76
00:03:22,270 --> 00:03:24,600
In the cases where we don't
have it, like with the Y

77
00:03:24,599 --> 00:03:26,889
chromosome, because you only
get it from your father in

78
00:03:26,889 --> 00:03:31,709
males, well, the defects and the
copy errors can actually

79
00:03:31,710 --> 00:03:33,120
accumulate over time.

80
00:03:33,120 --> 00:03:35,969
And in fact, the Y chromosome
in males is likely to become

81
00:03:35,969 --> 00:03:39,020
defective in a few million years
