123
00:05:23,730 --> 00:05:25,560
The reason is quite simple.

124
00:05:25,560 --> 00:05:29,240
If a species reproduces through
cloning, unless its

125
00:05:29,240 --> 00:05:31,910
generations go incredibly fast,
it can be a kind of

126
00:05:31,910 --> 00:05:33,130
sitting target.

127
00:05:33,129 --> 00:05:35,689
And it'll take on a heavy
parasite load.

128
00:05:35,689 --> 00:05:38,649
It's be quickly infected by
viruses and other sorts of

129
00:05:38,649 --> 00:05:42,129
things if it doesn't have some
kind of genetic defence.

130
00:05:42,129 --> 00:05:44,740
Sexual reproduction also
produces its own kind of

131
00:05:44,740 --> 00:05:46,040
selective pressure.

132
00:05:46,040 --> 00:05:49,030
We call this sexual selection.

133
00:05:49,029 --> 00:05:53,039
Sexual selection is the
intraspecific competition,

134
00:05:53,040 --> 00:05:54,850
that is the competition
with members of your

135
00:05:54,850 --> 00:05:56,950
own species to reproduce.

136
00:05:56,949 --> 00:06:00,170
Sexual selection arises because
there's a chance that

137
00:06:00,170 --> 00:06:03,280
not every member of a species
will get to reproduce.

138
00:06:03,279 --> 00:06:06,449
For an example of sexual
